cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses a neural network architecture for relational reasoning in visual inputs, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on visual inputs and proposes a method to extract relationships between entities in the input field. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely, as relational reasoning is a key component of intelligent behavior and the paper proposes a neural network architecture to solve this problem. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category, as the paper describes an end-to-end trainable model that learns to extract relationships from an attention mechanism over the input field. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely, but still possible, as the paper discusses the interpretability of the proposed model and how it can provide insights into the relationships between entities in the input field. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category, as the paper proposes a neural network architecture to solve a challenging problem in relational reasoning.
